title: Australia backs removal of Andrew from royal succession | 7NEWS
description: Prime Minister Anthony Albanese has written to UK Prime Minister Keir Starmer expressing support for removing Andrew Mountbatten-Windsor from the line of succession to the British and Australian throne. The move follows revelations of an email trail showing Prince Andrew's relationship with convicted paedophile Jeffrey Epstein. Currently, Andrew remains in the line of succession despite being stripped of royal titles, and could become king if Prince William, Prince Harry and their children die or refuse the crown. title: Severe rain alerts issued across four states | 7NEWS
description: Severe weather is forecast across Victoria, South Australia, Queensland and New South Wales, with the Bureau of Meteorology issuing multiple alerts. Victorian areas including Bendigo, Melbourne, Shepparton and Traralgon are expected to experience intense rainfall of one millimetre per minute. Heavy rain and potential flooding are also predicted for inland South Australia, Queensland and the Upper Western District of New South Wales, with conditions intensifying throughout the afternoon. title: Two-thirds of returning ISIS brides headed to Victoria | 7NEWS
description: Reports indicate two-thirds of ISIS brides seeking to return to Australia from a Syrian camp will be resettled in Victoria. The Victorian government has not confirmed specific numbers, stating applications are assessed individually, while NSW Premier Chris Minns revealed approximately one-third of 11 brides and 23 children will return to New South Wales. State and federal governments are conducting meetings to determine reintegration strategies, particularly regarding medical care and education for the children.
